## Preamble — Licensing Overview
This software distribution contains two types of components, each covered by a different license:

1. **MIT-licensed source code** — Headers, examples, and any files explicitly marked as MIT are open-source under the permissive MIT License.  
2. **Proprietary binaries** — All compiled libraries (`.dll`, `.lib`, `.so`, `.dylib`), models, and other compiled assets are **not open-source** and are provided under the Proprietary Binary License below.

You must comply with the terms of the license applicable to each component.

